I went for your suggestion to update to latest trunk and that solved t=
he problem.

Thanks a lot!

--- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Gordon =
Mohr <gojomo@...> wrote:
>
> This looks like it could be another manifestat=
ion of an issue that was 
> introduced by Oracle with JDK6u23/JDK6u24. The =
behavior of 
> GZIPInputStream was changed, and another bug in handling the=
 GZIP 
> 'extra' fields as we use in (W)ARC writing introduced.
> 
> The la=
test H3 source in SV trunk has a workaround, but the H3.0.0 
> release sour=
ce still relies on the older GZIPInputStream behavior.
> 
> So, if you are =
encountering this with JDK6u23/JDK6u24, some options are to:
> 
> (1) Go ba=
ck to JDK6u22 or earlier; or
> 
> (2) Use the latest source from SVN trunk.=

> 
> Unless you already have experience/confidence in the earlier code, I =

> recommend course (2) for active developers. You will sometimes encounter=
 
> new issues that exist only in the actively-developed code, but you'll 
=
> also have the advantage of the latest fixes/features, and be more ready 
=
> for your extensions to work in the next official release.
> 
> - Gordon @=
 IA
>
